# 🧠 BrainUp – AI LinkedIn Content Generator

> An autonomous AI agent that researches recent news, writes LinkedIn content, generates carousel slides, and delivers everything directly to Telegram.

---

# Why I Built This

Publishing consistently on LinkedIn is one of the highest ROI marketing activities for a small business.

The problem is that creating high-quality posts every week requires a surprising amount of work:

- Finding relevant news
- Researching trustworthy sources
- Writing engaging content
- Creating carousel slides
- Formatting everything
- Preparing visuals

I wanted to automate the entire content creation pipeline while keeping full editorial control.

Instead of publishing automatically, the workflow delivers ready-to-review content directly to Telegram.

---

# The Problem

Most LinkedIn creators spend more time creating content than interacting with their audience.

Every post requires:

- research
- writing
- design
- formatting
- translation

This quickly becomes unsustainable for founders and small teams.

---

# The Solution

This workflow acts as an AI content assistant.

Every week it:

1. Finds recent industry news.
2. Generates a LinkedIn post.
3. Creates a carousel when needed.
4. Produces French and English versions.
5. Builds visual slides automatically.
6. Sends everything to Telegram for review.

---

# Workflow Overview

```text
Schedule

      │

      ▼

Search recent news (Perplexity)

      │

      ▼

Extract useful information

      │

      ▼

GPT-4o writes the post

      │

      ▼

Generate carousel slides

      │

      ▼

Convert HTML → Images

      │

      ▼

Deliver to Telegram
```

---

# Weekly Content Strategy

The workflow follows a fixed publishing schedule.

## Monday

### Educational Carousel

Goal:

Teach a simple automation concept to non-technical SME owners.

---

## Wednesday

### Proof Post

Goal:

Show a real business result or automation success story.

Focus:

- ROI
- Before / After
- Business value

---

## Friday

### Reflection Post

Goal:

Share an opinion or industry trend about AI and automation.

---

# Step-by-Step

## 1. Scheduled Trigger

The workflow automatically starts three times per week.

Each trigger corresponds to a different content strategy.

---

## 2. Perplexity Research

Perplexity searches for recent information published during the last week.

The workflow retrieves:

- title
- source
- publication date
- summary

This guarantees that posts are based on fresh information instead of static prompts.

---

## 3. GPT-4o Content Generation

GPT receives:

- today's content type
- current news
- publishing guidelines
- formatting rules

It generates structured JSON containing:

- French version
- English version
- hashtags
- sources
- carousel slides (if applicable)

---

## 4. Carousel Generation

For educational posts:

GPT creates:

- Hook
- 5–8 slides
- Call to action

Each slide becomes an HTML page.

---

## 5. HTML → Image

Each HTML slide is converted into a high-resolution square image.

This removes the need for Canva or manual design work.

---

## 6. Telegram Delivery

The final output includes:

- LinkedIn post
- Carousel
- French version
- English version
- Sources

Everything arrives in Telegram ready for review.

Nothing is published automatically.

---

# Technologies

- n8n
- GPT-4o
- Perplexity API
- Telegram API
- HTML/CSS
- HCTI
- JavaScript

---

# Business Benefits

This workflow:

- reduces content creation time
- keeps posting consistent
- ensures posts rely on recent information
- automatically creates visuals
- centralizes content review

Instead of spending several hours preparing a LinkedIn post, the entire first draft is ready within minutes.

---

# Why Telegram?

Telegram acts as the human validation layer.

The workflow intentionally stops before publishing.

This allows:

- proofreading
- editing
- strategic decisions
- quality control

---

# Current Limitations

This workflow intentionally does NOT:

- publish directly to LinkedIn;
- respond to comments;
- analyze post performance;
- schedule LinkedIn posts;
- generate custom illustrations with AI;
- adapt posts using historical engagement data.

The objective is to accelerate content creation—not replace editorial judgment.

---

# Future Improvements

Future versions could include:

- LinkedIn API publishing
- Performance analytics
- AI-generated illustrations
- Personal writing style learning
- A/B testing
- Viral hook optimization
- Engagement prediction
- Content calendar generation

---

# Business Impact

This automation transforms LinkedIn content creation from a manual, multi-hour process into a structured AI-assisted workflow.

Instead of replacing creativity, it automates research, drafting and formatting so that creators can focus on refining ideas and engaging with their audience.

